		<title lang="en"><![CDATA[jqueryUI Login modal 1.0.95]]></title>
		<description lang="en"><![CDATA[installs a simple jquery based modal login dialogue using jQueryUI. it is highly theme-able and lightweight.

once it is installed that is it, refresh you style and it should be visible. 

If you want to change the theme you must edit the styles/ your template /templates/jqueryui/jqueryui.html

and to edit the modal popup to add extra html and stuff then edit the loginfrom.html in the same location]]></description>
		<author-notes lang="en"><![CDATA[To change to another style you must edit the styles / (relevant template path) /template/jqueryui/jqueryui.html

and find the line

<link type='text/css' href='{ROOT_PATH}js/jqueryui/css/vader/jquery-ui-1.8.22.custom.css' rel='stylesheet' media='screen' />

all you need to do is change the name of the css folder (in this line above it is vader)

to any from the list below. so if we chose redmond the new line would look like

<link type='text/css' href='{ROOT_PATH}js/jqueryui/css/redmond/jquery-ui-1.8.22.custom.css' rel='stylesheet' media='screen' />

